The cabinet shall issue a certification as a mitigation contractor to any person who:
Submits a complete and accurate application for certification on a form prescribed by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation;
Pays the certification fee established by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation within the following restrictions:
An initial certification fee shall not exceed two hundred fifty dollars ($250);
An annual renewal fee shall not exceed two hundred fifty dollars ($250);
A duplicate certificate fee shall not exceed twenty dollars ($20); and
A late renewal fee shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
Provides the cabinet with documentation of successful completion of a cabinet-approved radon mitigation course and exam;
For renewal of certification, provides proof of completion of at least eight (8) hours of continuing education credit per year;
Submits a quality control program plan that meets the minimum standard operating procedures requirements established by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation; and
Furnishes evidence of financial responsibility to the cabinet consisting of a liability insurance policy that satisfies the requirements of KRS 211.9113.

A mitigation contractor shall:
Ensure all mitigations are conducted in accordance with mitigation standard operating procedures established by an administrative regulation promulgated by the cabinet;
Maintain a quality control program plan that meets the minimum standard operating procedures requirements established by the cabinet through promulgation of an administrative regulation;
Ensure all mitigation activities are conducted under the general supervision of an individual certified to conduct radon mitigation;
Ensure post-mitigation measurement is conducted by a person certified to conduct measurement; and
Ensure all radon mitigation systems repaired or altered on or after January 1, 2013, meet the mitigation standard operating procedures established by an administrative regulation promulgated by the cabinet.
